title: Delta evacuates plane in Jamaica after faulty report of fire
text:
Delta evacuates plane in Jamaica after faulty report of fire Last updated 14:17, October 13 2015 Jamaica Gleaner/Twitter 
Passengers use emergency exits to get off Delta flight 304 after cargo on board caught fire on runway 
A Delta Air Lines plane aborted takeoff in Jamaica after a fire was reported in its cargo area, forcing 160 people and six crew members to evacuate the commercial jetliner which was scheduled to fly from Montego Bay to Atlanta. 
Nobody was injured in the incident at Sangster International Airport in the northern tourist city of Montego Bay. A Delta spokeswoman said the flight-deck warning was not accurate and there was no fire. 
Photos posted on the Jamaica Gleaner's website show passengers using emergency chutes on the Boeing 737 to get off the aircraft and onto the runway. PHOTO: Emergency vehicles parked near Delta flight 304 on which a fire broke out at Sangster Airport this afternoon. pic.twitter.com/V7FFFg0Lah
